# üéì Multi-Semester Timetable Scheduler Guide

## üÜï New Multi-Semester Features

### **1. Semester Selection**
- Switch between **1st, 3rd, 5th, and 7th semesters**
- Each semester has **independent data**
- Data is **automatically saved** when switching semesters

### **2. Teacher Collision Prevention**
- System prevents teachers from being scheduled in **multiple semesters at the same time**
- Example: If Prof. Sharma teaches Semester 1 at Monday P1, he cannot teach Semester 3 at Monday P1

### **3. Sample Data Loader**
- Click **"Load Sample Data"** to populate semester with realistic data
- Each semester has different subjects and structure
- Customize after loading to fit your needs

## üìö Semester-Specific Characteristics

### **Semester 1 (Foundation)**
**Focus:** Basic Sciences & Programming Fundamentals

**Typical Subjects:**
- Mathematics-I (5 periods)
- Physics (4 periods) + Physics Lab (2 periods)
- Chemistry (4 periods) + Chemistry Lab (2 periods)
- Engineering Graphics (4 periods)
- Programming in C (3 periods) + C Lab (2 periods)
- English (3 periods)

**Special Features:**
- More common activities (Orientation, Workshops)
- Basic lab work (3 labs total)
- Foundation teachers who may also teach other semesters

**Common Classes:**
- Orientation sessions
- Basic workshops

---

### **Semester 3 (Core CS)**
**Focus:** Data Structures, OS, Digital Logic

**Typical Subjects:**
- Mathematics (5 periods)
- Data Structures & Algorithms (4 periods) + DSA Lab (4 periods)
- Operating Systems (4 periods) + OS Lab (2 periods)
- Advanced Digital Logic Design (4 periods) + ADLD Lab (4 periods)
- Business Communication (3 periods)
- Digital Technology Lab (2 periods)

**Special Features:**
- Heavy lab component (3 major labs)
- Specific lab rooms (KOTAK1 for OS, KOTAK2 for DSA, CBL1 for ADLD)
- Core CS faculty

**Common Classes:**
- Usually none (focus on technical skills)

---

### **Semester 5 (Advanced Topics)**
**Focus:** Database, Theory, AI & Electives

**Typical Subjects:**
- DBMS (3 periods) + DBMS Lab (2 periods)
- Theory of Computation (3 periods) + TOC Lab (2 periods)
- POME (3 periods)
- AIML (3 periods) + AIML Lab (2 periods)
- Basket Course (3 periods)
- Counselling (1 period)

**Special Features:**
- **Flexible Half-Day Schedule:** 4 days are half-days (P1-P4 only), 1 day is full day with Lab in afternoon
- **Labs:** One lab per week (rotates or scheduled on the full day)
- **Dedicated Lab Rooms:** Database Lab, AIML Lab, TOC Lab

**Common Classes:**
- None (focused on academics)

---

### **Semester 7 (Specialization)**
**Focus:** ML, Cloud, IoT, Blockchain, Projects

**Typical Subjects:**
- Machine Learning (4 periods) + ML Lab (2 periods)
- Cloud Computing (3 periods)
- Blockchain Technology (3 periods)
- Internet of Things (3 periods) + IoT Lab (2 periods)
- Cyber Security (4 periods)
- Major Project Work (4 periods - LAB)
- Electives (3 periods)

**Special Features:**
- Heavy project component
- Industry-oriented electives
- Placement preparation activities
- Guest faculty and industry experts

**Common Classes:**
- Industry Talks (Wednesday P5)
- Placement Training (Friday P2-P3, 2 periods)
- Project reviews

## üîÑ How to Use Multi-Semester Feature

### **Step 1: Select Semester**
```
Click dropdown ‚Üí Select desired semester (1/3/5/7)
```

### **Step 2: Load Sample Data (Optional)**
```
Click "Load Sample Data" ‚Üí Confirm ‚Üí Data populated
```

### **Step 3: Customize Data**
```
Add/remove classes, subjects, teachers as needed
Modify periods, types, classroom assignments
```

### **Step 4: Add Data for Other Semesters**
```
Switch to different semester
Add classes, subjects, teachers
Repeat for all active semesters
```

### **Step 5: Generate Timetable**
```
Select the semester you want to generate
Click "Generate Timetable"
System automatically checks ALL semesters for teacher conflicts
```

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Teacher Collision Detection

### **How It Works:**
1. System collects data from ALL semesters with active classes
2. When generating for Semester 3, checks if teachers are busy in Semesters 1, 5, 7
3. Automatically avoids scheduling conflicts

### **Example Scenario:**
```
Semester 1: Prof. Sharma teaches Math at Monday P1
Semester 3: System will NOT schedule Prof. Sharma at Monday P1

This ensures Prof. Sharma can teach both semesters without conflict
```

### **Shared Teachers:**
Many teachers teach across semesters:
- Foundation faculty (Sem 1) may teach core courses (Sem 3)
- Specialized faculty (Sem 5, 7) may share elective courses
- Lab instructors may handle multiple semester labs

## üéØ Best Practices

### **1. Plan Shared Resources First**
```
Identify teachers who teach multiple semesters
Add their subjects in all relevant semesters
Generate in order: 1 ‚Üí 3 ‚Üí 5 ‚Üí 7
```

### **2. Designate Specific Lab Rooms**
```
Semester 1: Physics Lab, Chemistry Lab, C Lab
Semester 3: KOTAK1, KOTAK2, CBL1
Semester 5: Database Lab, AIML Lab, TOC Lab
Semester 7: ML Lab, IoT Lab, Project Lab
```

### **3. Common Classes Coordination**
```
Avoid scheduling common classes at same time across semesters
Example: Don't have Sem 1 Orientation AND Sem 7 Industry Talk both at Mon P1
This frees up faculty and resources
```

### **4. Friday Half-Day Consistency**
```
All semesters: Friday only has P1-P4
Plan lighter load on Fridays
Good for: Common activities, seminars, guest lectures
```

## üìä Sample Weekly Structure

### **Semester 1 - Monday**
```
P1: Orientation (ALL classes) ‚Üê Common Activity
P2: Mathematics-I - Dr. Sharma - R101
--- BREAK ---
P3: Physics Lab (2 periods) - Dr. Patel - Physics Lab
P4: Physics Lab (cont.)
--- LUNCH ---
P5: Programming in C - Prof. Gupta - R102
P6: Engineering Graphics - Prof. Reddy - R103
```

### **Semester 3 - Monday**
```
P1: MATH - SUMA - RVUF001 ‚Üê Dr. Sharma is busy in Sem 1
P2: FREE
--- BREAK ---
P3: DSA_LAB (2 periods) - DEEPAMALA - KOTAK2
P4: DSA_LAB (cont.)
--- LUNCH ---
P5: BC - T4 - RVUF003
P6: FREE
```

### **Semester 5 - Monday (Half-Day Example)**
```
P1: DBMS - Prof. Meena - RVUF104
P2: TOC - Prof. Lakshmi - RVUF104
--- BREAK ---
P3: AIML - Dr. Venkat - RVUF104
P4: POME - Dr. Ravi - RVUF104
--- LUNCH ---
P5: FREE (Half-Day)
P6: FREE (Half-Day)
```

### **Semester 7 - Monday**
```
P1: Machine Learning - Dr. Priya - R301
P2: Cloud Computing - Prof. Anand - R302
--- BREAK ---
P3: Project Work (2 periods) - Various - Project Lab
P4: Project Work (cont.)
--- LUNCH ---
P5: Cyber Security - Prof. Krishna - R301
P6: Blockchain - Prof. Suresh - R302
```

## üöÄ Quick Start Workflow

### **For Fresh Setup:**
1. Start with Semester 3 (default)
2. Click "Load Sample Data"
3. Review and customize
4. Switch to Semester 1
5. Load sample data
6. Switch to Semester 5
7. Load sample data
8. Switch to Semester 7
9. Load sample data
10. Go back to Semester 3
11. Click "Generate Timetable"

### **For Existing Data:**
1. Select semester
2. Add your classes, subjects, teachers
3. Add classrooms and common classes
4. Repeat for other semesters
5. Generate timetable for desired semester

## üí° Pro Tips

‚ú® **Consistent Teacher Names:** Use exact same name across semesters for collision detection
‚ú® **Lab Room Strategy:** Create specific lab rooms for each major lab subject
‚ú® **Common Activities:** Schedule at different times across semesters to avoid resource conflicts
‚ú® **Data Persistence:** Your data is saved automatically when switching semesters
‚ú® **Generation Order:** Generate lower semesters first, then higher ones
‚ú® **Teacher Availability:** Some teachers exclusively for one semester, others shared

## üéì Curriculum Progression

**Semester 1:** Foundation ‚Üí Basic Sciences + Intro Programming
**Semester 3:** Core CS ‚Üí DS, OS, Digital Logic
**Semester 5:** Advanced ‚Üí Networks, DB, Web, AI
**Semester 7:** Specialization ‚Üí ML, Cloud, IoT, Projects

Each semester builds on the previous, with increasing specialization and project work!

